</program>

<p>
<idx><h>description</h></idx>
Documentation comments should begin with a <em>description</em> of the class or method, followed by the tags.
These two sections are separated by a blank line (not counting the \relax<c>*</c>).
</p>

<p>
For methods, we can use <c>@param</c> and <c>@return</c> to provide information about parameters and return values:
</p>

